name: USS Anchorage (Azur Lane)
description:
Updated Mar/11/2023:

Tried out the LoHA (LoCon, aka LyCORIS as per its creator's preferred but eccentric name) format for Anchorage's update. Quality is indeed impressive and switching to this training method takes surprisingly little time to adapt to. I strongly recommend other trainers to give it a go.

  • IMPORTANT: This extension for webui from LoHA's creator is required to access LoHA models: https://github.com/KohakuBlueleaf/a1111-sd-webui-locon. Only then LoHA will be read and function just like any other LoRA model. Place 'em where LoRAs reside, call 'em up the way you call LoRAs up, simple as that. Otherwise you'll get only the vanilla image delivered by checkpoint with errors in the console.

An obvious defect however, is that due to the very high level of details it acquired through training, some features I thought to be unique to her original costume (the chest harness as I noticed) would pop up somewhat more often when not prompted to do so. Not sure if negative prompting could fix this or I need to further refine captioning.

Release V2.0 works well on full weight (1.0) and here are prompts for replicating her original costume. Copy & paste it for ease of use, as skimming chara/outfits into a single keyword is NOT remotely as flexible despite it surely is convenient:

  • acrgazln, very long hair, headgear, blue coat, cleavage, midriff, off shoulder, very long sleeves, sleeves past fingers, short shorts, thigh strap, black footwear,

Features USS Anchorage from Azur Lane in her original costume, trained on ACertainModel.

Release V1 has been tested and works with high level of flexibility on high weight range (0.7-0.9), for lower weight details such as her eye color or harness may become inconsistent.

Suggested Prompts:

  • Base: acrgazln, headgear, blue coat, sleeves past fingers, short black shorts, black footwear
